{
  "texts": [
    "The system generates virtual constraints to guide the surgeon in the milling operations and avoid burring the bone outside the predefined areas [179].",
    "A different example of a semi-autonomous robot used in orthopaedic surgery is Navio [175], from Smith & Nephew (Fig. 6c).",
    "Navio is a telerobot designed to assist surgeons with knee replacement surgery without requiring a CT scan to plan the surgery.",
    "Instead, during the procedure, Navio builds a 3D model of the patient's knee.",
    "This information helps the surgeon determine the correct size and position of the implant.The successful introduction of robots in orthopaedic surgery is possible thanks to the rigid nature of bones and consistent imaging registration."
  ]
}